# Deploy and verify after desktop / web fixes

Git commit + push updates source only. Operators run **installed binaries**
under `C:\Program Files\AIC\…` and **browser URLs** served by a running daemon.
A change is **incomplete** until the rebuilt artifact is on that path and confirmed.

> **Mandatory deploy.** When an agent finishes work on a shipping binary or GUI
> surface listed below, it **must** rebuild, copy into the installed Program
> Files tree (or restart the dev server the operator uses), and verify timestamps
> **in the same turn** — before telling the user to retest. Per-product plan
> docs must **not** say "do not auto-deploy" or "wait for explicit go-ahead";
> that contradicts this rule.

## Desktop GUIs (elevation, configurators, launchers)

Applies to every Win32 / Tauri surface launched from Desktop or Start Menu:

- `pim-offline-client-elevate-{win32,tauri}`
- `pim-offline-client-configurator-{win32,tauri}`
- `pim-offline-server-configurator-{win32,tauri}`
- `pim-product-launcher-win32`

### Required loop (do not skip steps)

1. **Rebuild** the changed crate (`cargo build --release` in `src-tauri` for Tauri;
   crate root for Win32). Stage FIPS DLLs per `fips-dll-staging.mdc` when the
   binary links `aws-lc-rs/fips`.
2. **Deploy** the release `.exe` (and sidecar DLLs) into Program Files:
   - Agent: `C:\Program Files\AIC\OfflinePimAgent\`
   - Server configurators: `C:\Program Files\AIC\OfflinePimServer\`
   Copy **both** MSI canonical names and cargo aliases when they differ (example:
   `pim-offline-elevate-tauri.exe` **and**
   `pim-offline-client-elevate-tauri.exe`). Prefer
   `pim-installers/scripts/Install-StagedAgentBinaries.ps1` for full agent sets;
   single-binary hotfix may copy directly from `target\release\`.
3. **Verify shortcut target** — resolve the operator's `.lnk` (Desktop, Start
   Menu, taskbar pin) and confirm `Target` points at the deployed path you just
   overwrote. Report canonical name vs alias if they differ.
4. **Verify installed timestamp** — `Get-Item` on the deployed exe must be
   **newer than** the pre-fix copy; include `LastWriteTime` and size in the
   status reply.
5. **Tell the operator** to close any already-open window before retesting (old
   process keeps the old build loaded).

### Forbidden

- Declaring a desktop bug "fixed" or a redesign "done" after push only.
- Skipping Program Files deploy because the user did not say "install" in the
  same message — deploy is the default completion step for GUI work.
- Assuming `target\release\…` is what the shortcut runs without copying to
  Program Files.
- Deploying only the cargo alias when the MSI canonical name also exists (or
  vice versa).
- Plan docs or agent prompts that forbid auto-deploy to Program Files.

## Offline server web admin (`pim-offline-server/ui`)

The React admin UI is embedded at **server build time** (`build.rs` runs
`npm run build --prefix ui` unless `AUTO_BUILD_UI=false`).

### Required loop

1. **Rebuild UI + server** — set `AUTO_BUILD_UI=true` (or unset) when `ui/`
   changed; then `cargo build --release` in `pim-offline-server`.
2. **Deploy** — copy `pim-offline-server.exe` (and FIPS DLL) to
   `C:\Program Files\AIC\OfflinePimServer\`, or restart a `cargo run` dev
   instance if that is the operator's test target.
3. **Restart** the Windows service (`aic-offline-server-service`) or the dev
   process so the new static bundle is loaded.
4. **Confirm site availability** — HTTP GET the operator URL (typically
   `https://localhost:8443/` or the configured `SERVER_PUBLIC_URL`); confirm
   `200` / redirect to the admin shell and that the changed screen or asset is
   present. For API-only changes, hit the affected admin route with auth.
5. **Push** source after deploy verification when the user asked for commit/push;
   push does not replace steps 1–4.

### Forbidden

- Editing only `ui/src` and expecting the running server to pick it up without a
  rebuild + restart.
- Leaving `AUTO_BUILD_UI=false` during a UI-fix session.

## Status reply shape

End every desktop/web fix turn with:

| Artifact | Deploy path | Shortcut target (if known) | LastWriteTime | Verified |
| -------- | ----------- | -------------------------- | ------------- | -------- |

If deploy failed (file lock, elevation denied), say so and stop — do not claim
the operator can retest yet.

